     byte-offset rune truncation (no full []rune alloc).
  11. Consolidated the 30s timeout into exported rss.DefaultTimeout.
- Re-review found one HIGH and one missed LOW, both fixed:
  HIGH: data race on p.src validators (Fetch write / SourceState read) under
        concurrent same-Provider Fetch — fixed with a sync.Mutex (snapshot
        under lock, never held across network I/O) + a -race regression test
        (TestFetch_concurrent_noRace, passes 20x).
  LOW: opml_test.go id1[:4] -> strings.HasPrefix.
  Plus documented the content-hash native-id volatility caveat.
- Final verdicts: functional resolved, quality PASS, performance PASS,
  ADR NOT-APPLICABLE (standalone Go project, no Fullbay infra).

Decisions
---------
- ImportOPML returns []FeedRef{Source, URL} (not []model.Source) because feedID
  is a one-way hash and the registry needs the URL to build a provider.
- A fresh gofeed.Parser per Fetch + a mutex over the validators make Provider
  concurrency-safe ahead of the Step 07 parallel sync engine.
- Per-feed concurrency in dump, FTS5 search, and rejecting non-positive
  sync_interval remain deferred (Step 07 / later phases).
